</section><section data-mw-section-id="59" id="mwBNA"><h2 id="Notes">Notes</h2>
<div class="reflist " style=" list-style-type: lower-alpha;" about="#mwt824" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"notelist","href":"./Template:Notelist"},"params":{},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBNE">
<div class="mw-references-wrap" typeof="mw:Extension/references" about="#mwt1208" data-mw='{"name":"references","attrs":{"group":"lower-alpha","responsive":"1"},"body":{"html":""}}'><ol class="mw-references references" data-mw-group="lower-alpha"><li about="#cite_note-3" id="cite_note-3"><a href="./Charlemagne#cite_ref-3" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-3" class="mw-reference-text">In <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Latin_language" title="Latin language" id="mwBNI" class="mw-redirect">Latin</a>: <i lang="la" id="mwBNM">Karolus</i><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Latin-language_text" id="mwBNQ"/> or <i id="mwBNU">Carolus</i>, whence Charles. The French form <i lang="fr" title="French language text" id="mwBNY">Charlemagne</i><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_French-language_text" id="mwBNc"/> and the Italian <i lang="it" title="Italian language text" id="mwBNg">Carlo Magno</i><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Italian-language_text" id="mwBNk"/> or <i lang="it" title="Italian language text" id="mwBNo">Carlomagno</i><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Italian-language_text" id="mwBNs"/> come from his nickname <i lang="la" title="Latin language text" id="mwBNw">Carolus Magnus</i><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Latin-language_text" id="mwBN0"/> ("Charles the Great").</span></li><li about="#cite_note-4" id="cite_note-4"><a href="./Charlemagne#cite_ref-4" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-4" class="mw-reference-text">Additional birth years for Charlemagne include 747 and 748. There is scholarly debate over this topic. See Karl Ferdinand Werner, <i id="mwBN4">Das Geburtsdatum Karls des Großen</i>, in <i id="mwBN8">Francia</i> 1, 1973, pp. 115–157 (<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://mdzx.bib-bvb.de/francia/Blatt_bsb00016275,00115.html" id="mwBOA">online</a>  <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20131117074120/http://mdzx.bib-bvb.de/francia/Blatt_bsb00016275%2C00115.html" id="mwBOE">Archived</a> 17 November 2013 at the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine" id="mwBOI">Wayback Machine</a><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Webarchive_template_wayback_links" id="mwBOM"/>);<br id="mwBOQ"/>Matthias Becher: <i id="mwBOU">Neue Überlegungen zum Geburtsdatum Karls des Großen</i>, in: <i id="mwBOY">Francia</i> 19/1, 1992, pp. 37–60 (<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://mdzx.bib-bvb.de/francia/Blatt_bsb00016296,00047.html" id="mwBOc">online</a>  <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20131117074146/http://mdzx.bib-bvb.de/francia/Blatt_bsb00016296%2C00047.html" id="mwBOg">Archived</a> 17 November 2013 at the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine" id="mwBOk">Wayback Machine</a><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Webarchive_template_wayback_links" id="mwBOo"/>);</span></li><li about="#cite_note-8" id="cite_note-8"><a href="./Charlemagne#cite_ref-8" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-8" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" id="mwBOs">Papst Johannes Paul II (2004). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120117151907/http://www.karlspreis.de/preistraeger/seine_heiligkeit_papst_johannes_paul_ii/ansprache_von_seiner_heiligkeit_papst_johannes_paul_ii.html" id="mwBOw">"Ansprache von seiner Heiligkeit Papst Johannes Paul II"</a> (in German). Internationaler Karlspreis zu Aachen. Archived from <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" hre