wBdM">Butt, John J. (1 January 2002). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=bQlJP9O9hKkC" id="mwBdQ"><i id="mwBdU">Daily Life in the Age of Charlemagne</i></a>. Greenwood Publishing Group. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBdY">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBdc"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/9780313316685" title="Special:BookSources/9780313316685" id="mwBdg">9780313316685</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Daily+Life+in+the+Age+of+Charlemagne&amp;rft.pub=Greenwood+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2002-01-01&amp;rft.isbn=9780313316685&amp;rft.aulast=Butt&amp;rft.aufirst=John+J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DbQlJP9O9hKkC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACharlemagne" class="Z3988" about="#mwt128" id="mwBdk"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt128" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBdo"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-59" id="cite_note-59"><a href="./Charlemagne#cite_ref-59" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-59" class="mw-reference-text">Runciman, Steven. "The Empress Irene the Athenian." Medieval Women. Ed. Derek Baker. Oxford: Ecclesiastical History Society, 1978.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBecher2005122-60" id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEBecher2005122-60"><a href="./Charlemagne#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBecher2005122_60-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-FOOTNOTEBecher2005122-60" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Charlemagne#CITEREFBecher2005" id=